description:
With a 25-year history in the entertainment industry, Ralph Carrs credentials and ability speak for themselves.
With groundbreaking success as a business manager, independent publisher, tour promoter,  it is no surprise that Carr is one of the most sought-after pioneers in the industry.
Known for his no-nonsense approach, Ralph has been instrumental in the careers of many of Australia's most successful artists, entertainers, celebrities and sporting personalities including Tina Arena, Vanessa Amorosi, Richard Wilkins, Mark Vincent and Dustin Martin.
RCM Artists have achieved an astronomical level of success under Ralphs guidance that include numerous ARIA awards including Best Australian Adult Contemporary Record, Best Australian Single, Song of the Year, Highest Selling Australian Album, Highest Selling Australian Single and 11 number one ARIAs for albums and singles. 
In mid-2008, three RCM clients held a position in the Australian national Top 10 album charts in the same week; a feat never before achieved by an Australian management company.
In recent years Carr moved into Sport Management with RCM Sport. 
His client list includes prestigious players Dustin Martin (Richmond Football Club), Nick Haynes (Greater Western Sydney) and Shai Bolton (Richmond Football Club). 
Nothing could demonstrate Carrs prowess in this field more than in his work with Dustin Martin, negotiating a record-breaking contract extension combined with an incredible year for the player, made Dustin one of the most successful players in the history of the AFL.
The creation of RCM Touring saw the industry icon add to his already impressive repertoire, building a team of passionate accomplished concert promoters. 
Whether a national arena tour, an intimate show or exhibition, the extensive experience Ralph brings with him to each project is crucial.
To quote from Kate Ceberano’s autobiography: “He has an incredible work ethic and would take a bullet for an artist he really believes in”
jobDescription:
Ralph has been involved in the careers of many of Australia's most successful artists including Tina Arena, Vanessa Amarosi, Richard Wilkins, Kate Ceberano, Mark Vincent, Cosentino, Paris Wells, Jon Stevens, Sally Cooper, Bonnie Anderson, Rick Price, Pseudo Echo, Deborah Conway and more!

Encompassing the same level of service that his entertainment clients have grown to expect, Ralph also provides his sporting client with endorsement and appearance sourcing, personal support and financial planning services through RCM Sport.

To quote from Kate Cebrano's autobiography: "He has an incredible work ethic and would take a bullet for an artist he really believes in". The work and story continues…

description: Ever since i was a kid i aways wanted to be the best at whatever it was i was doing. I didn't realise it then but my competitive nature and personal drive have been part of the reason for my success as a professional athlete. i love challenges and love meeting new people. I don't take myself to seriously and love to have a laugh. Although i am seen as a bit of a larikan there is a professional side to me that i had to adapt to over the years, as i got more experience at St Kilda football club. I naturally moved into a leadership position that i really enjoyed and with that came great responsibility. over the past 13 years i have matured quickly and have been able to channel my energy into the things i love, family and football. I have taken those two things that are close to my heart as far as i can and now i am ready for the next phase in my life. I like to keep things simple, i have enough experience and personal confidence to take on just about everything. I want to work on something that i am passionate about and whoever i am working with will get the best out of me.
jobDescription:
Hi All,

Just a quick note letting you all know that I have joined up with a good bunch of blokes who have sold their share in a larger cleaning company to start up an exciting company called Command 51.   

Command 51 offers cleaning, gardening and security services to the education, hospitality and commercial industries and at present we clean the Jimmy Grants and Hellenic restaurants in Melbourne. Further to that, Command 51 does all of the gardening for Hungry Jacks in NSW and on a daily basis clean over 100 sites from Brisbane, Sydney to Melbourne and everywhere in between. The main thing that sets Command 51 apart from most other service providers is the accountability that the team pride themselves on. Every venue that Command 51 services, regardless if it's cleaning, security or grounds has a client service manage allocated to look after that client, and it's that CSM's job to visit the site once a week and be contactable 7 days a week to make sure that the service that the client is paying for is delivered. That's where I slot in.

So if any of you know anybody  that is sick of not being able to contact their cleaners or gardeners or just want to make sure that they are paying the right price, please let me know and I will gladly give them a buzz to see how I can help them out.

Thanks in advance

jobDescription2:
I led and managed Red Hat's EMEA and North American Recruiting team helping to build a top-performing Talent Acquisition team utilising a joint Sourcer / Recruiter operating model to deliver top talent to our business. This enabled Red Hat's hugely exciting business' transformation from an operating system provider to a multi-product solutions provider.  In my 4 years at Red Hat my team scaled Red Hat from 4,500 to 13, 000 associates globally. 

My first and second-line reports were spread across 7 different office locations globally covering all Sales, Presales, Professional Services, Engineering, Product Management and Corporate hiring. 

Red Hat (NYSE: RHT) is an S&P 500 company achieving $13B USD with now 61 consecutive quarters of revenue growth and now 12,000 associates. We are the world’s leading provider of open source software solutions, using a community-powered approach to reliable and high-performing cloud, Linux, middleware, storage and virtualization technologies. Red Hat also offers award-winning support, training, and consulting services.

Red Hat is where passionate and creative people come to enjoy high-impact careers. As catalysts in communities of customers, contributors, and partners, we make better technology the open source way. The next IT revolution isn't about raw technology, it's about how people create, improve, and use it. People who understand that future are excited by it, and we empower them to make it happen.

description:
I grew up in Adelaide, South Australia completing high school with honours. I moved Perth, Western Australia in 2009 on a scholarship. I love the unknown, travelling has become a significant part of my life. 

I have completed my Bachelor of Journalism, Masters in Public Relations and Management and am currently completing my PhD in Broadcast Journalism. I am a very positive person, and surround myself with people with these common goals and attributes. I love to learn. I aim to seek as much knowledge from those around me as I can, soaking up the information like a sponge. I am passionately pursuing my presenting career with several projects currently underway. 

I am an international model based in Perth, experienced in glamour and swimwear photographic, catwalk, competitions, parades and promotions. I hold several national titles and appear regularly in publications worldwide. I also work as a stylist for many of Australia's leading photographers. 

With a love of all things fashionable, I have created my very own designer label "Delysha Daly Collection". This range features new innovative styles for lingerie and swimwear competition and event wear, coupled with slick dress designs for smart business wear. The label is set to launch at an exclusive VIP function at Gold Bar in Subiaco later November 2012.  

Interior design has always been a hobby for me, renovating our units was an opportunity to put plans into practice. Through this evolved my new business Style My Pad which is an online company that distributes the latest trends in furniture and bedding worldwide. I now oversee the sales team based Perth, Western Australia. 

My amazing husband, Eoin Daly, and I began a real estate portfolio together of which I presently manage also. 

Through effective and efficient management, all three of my businesses run autonomously, creating sufficient passive income to support my next exciting business plan. I consider myself a young entrepreneur.
jobDescription:
TV PRESENTING

Delysha started her presenting career at five years old, presenting the news and weather to her family through several comical home videos. 

As a Pembroke School Scholar, Delysha completed her Bachelor of Journalism and Masters in Public Relations and Management at the top of her class and is currently completing her PhD in Journalism in Perth, Western Australia. 

Delysha has hosted her very own radio show on Kalamunda Radio Station 102.5 in Western Australia. Delysha has also reported directly for Murdoch Radio News, West TV and has several featured segments on Radio Fremantle 107.9. 

As a journalist, Delysha is a keen writer and has reported as a music reviewer for RTR FM 92.1, a nightlife reporter for Barsandclubs.com and food critic for Menu Magazine.

MODELING

Delysha began her modeling career in her hometown of Adelaide, South Australia. Starting as an energetic promotional model, Delysha soon tackled Adelaide’s fashion industry, showcasing designers’ finest casual, evening and bridal wear in runway events and editorial photoshoots. 

After moving to Perth, Western Australia in 2009, Delysha’s modeling career intensified, collaborating with some of Australia’s best international photographers. 

Delysha places regularly in several of Perth’s National Modeling Competitions, recent ones include including Miss Lingerie and Lace, Miss Zoom TV, Miss Black Bikini and Miss All Stars. 

Delysha has appeared in numerous national lifestyle, fashion and mens magazines, calendars, merchandise and has recently featured internationally in Banzai Magazine (Japan), Elite Magazine (UK) and FHM (Turkey). 

In 2010, Delysha started her own modeling business in Perth.

Having a passion for swimwear and glamour photography, expect to see Delysha gracing the cover of your favourite magazine again soon.
jobDescription2:
Delysha Daly Collection is the newest Australian fashion label specialising in designer lingerie, swimwear and dresses. 

The collection features an array of stylish intimate wear and swimwear perfection for competition, parades and events.  

The collection also features the latest trends in smart dress wear and classy business wear for women. 

The label and corresponding website is set to be launched at an exclusive VIP event in 2013.

Equifax is a global information solutions company that uses trusted unique data, innovative analytics, technology and industry expertise to power organizations and individuals around the world by transforming knowledge into insights that help make more informed business and personal decisions. The company organizes, assimilates and analyzes data on more than 820 million consumers and more than 91 million businesses worldwide, and its database includes employee data contributed from more than 7,100 employers. Headquartered in Atlanta, Ga., Equifax operates or has investments in 24 countries in North America, Central and South America, Europe and the Asia Pacific region. It is a member of Standard & Poor's (S&P) 500® Index, and its common stock is traded on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the symbol EFX. Equifax employs approximately 9,900 employees worldwide.

description:
Oh hey! I’m Sarah, or SP, as most call me. 

I'm excited by people, culture, talent acquisition, employer brand, engagement, great relationships and ongoing learning… but sprinkle that with collaboration, cool tech and disruptive innovation!

I’m a decisive, creative influencer who is forward-thinking and ambitious - I like to challenge the status-quo. I have an outgoing, optimistic approach and I encourage others to work hard, play hard, collaborate and celebrate. A happy and engaged team is a high performing team and I believe that in nurturing this you add massive value to your business and how it is seen out in the market.

I thrive in workplaces that are fast-paced, supportive, inclusive, dynamic and encourage creativity and sharing new ideas. Basically, an employer who wants you to bring your authentic self to work every day.

As a self-proclaimed Talent Ninja, I understand the importance of employer brand, culture, diversity and creating an inclusive and collaborative environment where people feel valued and have a strong sense of belonging. I am passionate about building a strong employer brand that truly reflects the values and ethos of an employer whilst encouraging advocacy and attracting great talent for the long haul.

description:
Women around the world can now have an attractive, bikini-model body like Australia’s Ashy Bines. Bines has turned the secrets she learned during bikini competitions and into a comprehensive yet easy-to-follow program that can work for anyone. The Ashy Bines Clean Eating Diet Plan includes eating guidelines that help you to make the right food choices, along with sample meal plans, recipes, tips for ordering in restaurants and much more. The plan also includes information on how to develop a personal exercise program that fits your lifestyle. Ashy Bines’s plan teaches you how to make gradual changes that not only help you attain a healthy, attractive body but also keep it that way.

Women who purchase the Ashy Bines Clean Eating Diet Plan also gain access to an online members-only forum where they can get answers to questions, network with other women using the plan, and communicate with Bines herself. The forum provides ongoing 24-hour support, the opportunity to ask questions of certified personal trainers and dieticians, plus helpful advice, recipes and more. 

Those who desire an even more interactive program can sign up for one of the Ashy Bines 12-week Bikini Body Challenge packages. With each of these affordable packages you receive the Clean Eating Diet Plan, forum membership, support, and weekly testing, plus you get to participate in fun group training sessions. Training classes include activities like jogging, circuit training, cardio exercises, boxing, and stretching.

The Bikini Body Challenge classes are scheduled in cities across Australia. Choose from the 3-session-per-week Kick-Start package, the 6-session-per-week Step It Up package that also includes a one-on-one meeting with your trainer and a special iPhone app, or the exclusive Platinum level that includes all the Step It Up benefits plus a greatly reduced price for a one-year commitment. All packages include an Ashy Bines training singlet, wristband, and bumper sticker.
